# Card data conventions

See [DDR-0011](../../docs/design/decisions/0011-effect-enum-frozen-text-canonical.md):
the card's `text` field is the canonical rule. The `effects` and
`triggeredAbilities` fields are kept for the existing renderer, but are **not
required on new cards**, and **no new `EffectType` enum values are added**.

## Minimum fields for a new card

```ts
{
    name: { en: 'Card Name' },
    text: { en: <span>...canonical rule text...</span> },
    cost: 3,
    // employee: skills, level (JUNIOR | SENIOR), title
    // contract: requiredSkills, storyPoints
    // optional: printCount — copies in app Print view / PDF (default 1).
    // Starter deck templates often use `* MAX_PLAYER_COUNT` from
    // `src/lib/constants.ts` (per-seat copies).
}
```

## Text conventions

- **Standard icons** (in `text`, either emoji or `<Icons.X size={14} />`):
  - 💲 BUDGET, ⚙️ KNOWLEDGE, 💡 CREATIVITY, 🗒️ ORGANIZATION, ⭐ PRESTIGE.
- **Cost modifier**: `+💲💲` form (one icon per unit of value).
- **Triggered text**: `When [event]: [effect]` or `Each time [event]: [effect]` (repeating).
- **Passive stats**: rendered from `skills` / `requiredSkills`, **do not repeat in `text`**.
- **End-of-game prestige**: comes from the `prestige` field; **do not repeat in
  `text`** unless players need an explicit reminder (e.g. a hire with no other
  written abilities).

## Removed fields (see DDR-0006, DDR-0007)

- `sector` (Industry) — may stay on existing cards, **do not add to new cards**.
- `hobby` — may stay on existing cards, **do not add to new cards**.

## Level convention (DDR-0005)

Production employee `level`: **only `JUNIOR` or `SENIOR`**. `MEDIOR` does not
exist for MVP. Admin employees also receive a `level` field (`JUNIOR` |
`SENIOR`).
